        <item>
			<title>Class 10: The Second Noble Truth, the Cause of Suffering with Thich Chan Phap Hai</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://deerpark.libsyn.com/class-10-the-second-noble-truth-the-cause-of-suffering-with-thich-chan-phap-hai]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>Last week, we learned about the first turning of the wheel-the recognition of our suffering and our situation. &nbsp;With the second turning of the wheel, Thich Chan Phap Hai encourages us to explores the causes of our suffering. &nbsp;We learn more deeply about the three poisons-- Greed (or 'ever-seeking' or 'always wanting'), Hatred (or ill-will or 'closed-down heart') and ignorance or delusion (not ignorance as in lack of learning but in the inability to see things as they really are). &nbsp;These are the three roots of suffering that the 4 noble truths offered by the Buddha will transform leading to liberation. The weekly practices focus on 'bare recognition' or 'bare experience' and handout includes many important readings.</p>
<p>Tonight's talk is a beautiful offering of the dharma that is practical for us to use. &nbsp;It offers guideposts that help us on the journey in the Dharma that each of us must experience for ourselves. &nbsp;We hope you will find it immediately useful and effective.</p>]]></description>
