<p><em><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;">I am not caught in mere intellectual understanding</span></em><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;">Our Sister reminds us that we can learn to let go, that we already have everything we need inside of us. &nbsp;We can stop running, stop aiming, and make use of what we already have.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;">A good reflection is to look at our life right now and find out what is making us feel not free. &nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: &quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: black;">This beautiful sharing is closed with the deep insight, "Thank you for allowing myself to see myself more."</span></p>
