        <item>
			<title>Verse 6 of the 14 Verses on Meditation: Looking Deeply into the Heart of Reality</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://deerpark.libsyn.com/verse-6-of-the-14-verses-on-meditation-looking-deeply-into-the-heart-of-reality]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>
<p>Dear Friends on the Path,</p>
<p>Here is the teaching on Verse 6.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Verse 6</strong></span></p>
<p><em>Looking deeply into the heart of reality</em></p>
<p><em>to see the true nature of things,</em></p>
<p><em>practicing vipashyana enables me to let go</em></p>
<p><em>of everything I am searching for, my desires, and my fears.</em></p>
<p>Our sister shares the teaching with us that the practice is to be closer to our hearts. The more I know myself, the more I can connect with what is outside.</p>
<p>There are some wonderful suggestions for reflections that we can all benefit from too for the new year.</p>
<p>
<p><strong>Reflections: &nbsp;Ending a year and starting a new:</strong></p>
<p>- what nourishment did 2010 offer</p>
<p>- what were the challenges</p>
<p>- how do I aspire to continue</p>
<p>Happy New Year Everyone!! &nbsp;May your year be filled with peace and stability of living in the Present Moment.</p>
</p>
</p>]]></description>
